5 Beds  |  4 Full Baths  |  Residential


[Main Property Photo]


Open House
May 20, 2018 - 1:00PM to 4:00PM May 27, 2018 - 1:00PM to 4:00PM

Description

Come see this contemporary new construction with magnificent views and a newly added great backyard! This wonderful home in one of the most desirable areas in Orinda is truly one of a kind. Conveniently located with easy access to freeways, this gorgeous two-level +/-4,542 square foot home with 5 bedrooms and 4 full bathrooms sits on 1.14 acres. Bright and inviting with an exceptionally flexible layout for maximum usage. Beautiful large decks with panoramic views wrap around the house and flow into a flat and private backyard with a fantastic lawn area. Each level features a full master suite with hand-made tiles in the bathrooms, soaking tubs, separate showers, double vanities and spacious walk-in closets.

The quality and attention to details are exceptional in this home.  It is built to highest standards and consistently uses high-end materials throughout the house, even in the parts you don’t see. This is one of a kind, contemporary home that leaves nothing to be desired. Here are some of the highlights:

Wood floors throughout the house, no carpets anywhere. The stairs are stained to match the cabinetry.

Custom cabinets constructed with plywood boxes in the kitchen. Notice the grain-matched pantry doors. Custom floating cabinets in the hallway for elegant storage options.

The kitchen features a 9-foot-long waterfall island with Quartz countertops ("Cambria"). Thermador and Bosch appliances.

Thermostatic showers let you easily set desired shower water temperature without the need to change the water flow.

All windows are Anderson dual-pane windows.

A stylish "La Cantina" multi-slide door and 16 inches long gas fireplace in the main living room provide exceptional entertainment options.

All lights inside and outside the house are LED, helping you save energy while still giving you outstanding lighting.

The foundation is a pier foundation drilled to bedrock.

Two types of ("Hardy") siding on the house that is made of durable fire-proof cement-fiber composite, the Hardy Reveal siding is custom-cut to create a unique and modern look. No stucco used here.

Metal roof, which is not only much more durable than shingle composite roofs, it is also fire-proof and more energy-efficient with its light-absorbing and reflecting properties. It also better in resisting mold and algae.

The house features 2 complete separate heating and air conditioning systems, one for each floor to give the option to heat or cool each floor separately. The water heater has a build-in recirculation pump, ensuring immediate access to hot water when you want it.

The whole house is hard-wired with CAT5 and CAT6 cable, so you don't need to rely on wireless internet.

Notice the consistent high 10-foot ceilings upstairs and downstairs. Very rarely will you find consistently high ceilings in multiple story homes.

[Main Property Photo]


Open House
May 19, 2018 - 1:00PM to 4:00PM May 20, 2018 - 1:00PM to 4:00PM

Description

Transformed from top to bottom, inside and out, this absolutely enchanting home boasts all the charm of its circa 1916 heritage with a new modern sophistication. From the newly stuccoed exterior to the wide open floor plan all unified with espresso-hued hardwood floors, every inch has been touched with designer style while still recalling all the character of the original bungalow. There are 3 bedrooms, including a master suite much larger than expected for a home of this era. All of the finishes in the bathroom and kitchen, the wall colors, and moldings are perfectly selected with timeless appeal. Outside, the landscaping presents new beginnings as well with a border of colorful roses, new fencing, and a side patio accessed via a wall of stacking glass doors in the great room. Topping it all off is the homes premier location just two blocks from famed Burlingame Avenue, access to acclaimed Burlingame schools and situated midway between San Francisco and Silicon Valley.

Units have had some recent updates to kitchen & baths, dual pane windows. New exterior paint and gutters. A great opportunity to own in one of Berkeley's most desirable neighborhoods. Located on a tree-lined street near BART and shopping, minutes from Gourmet Ghetto and UC Berkeley campus... High Walk and Bike scores!

Description

Nestled on a serene cul-de-sac in the coveted Farm Hill Estates neighborhood, this recently remodeled contemporary home exhibits modern day living designed with clean lines and open spaces. The single level floor plan is highlighted by gorgeous hardwood flooring and large picture windows and doors that bring the outdoor spaces in. A divine master suite retreat is secluded on one wing of the home, while a second master suite plus two spacious bedrooms which share a hall bathroom are located on another. With a spectacular 11,700 sf level lot, you can enjoy entertaining guests year-round in the resort like setting featuring a sparkling pool/spa, shaded entertainment deck with a neighboring outdoor kitchen, bocce ball court and gas fire pit, plus an expansive artificial lawn with a raised deck. Plus with its ideal location and excellent Roy Cloud School, this is truly a special home that you will cherish!

Absolutely gorgeous - 2 years new - Craftsman inspired home is accentuated by chic modern appointments, dramatic ceiling height, large picture windows and oak wood flooring that stretches throughout. The spacious 5 bed, 4 bath, 3,312+/- sf floor plan is highlighted by formal living spaces on the main level that lead to the heart of the home - a great room attached with a culinary kitchen and breakfast nook that flows out to the recreational backyard. Welcome to this 4 Bedroom 3.5 bath home located in Central Atherton. Short distance to downtown Menlo Park. This home has an abundance of natural light through many skylights. Some of the many features include formal living room with gas fireplace, kitchen with granite counter tops, new appliances and a wine refrigerator for over 167 bottles. Large master suite with a state of the art bathroom, double sinks, bidet, double shower travertine floor, custom cabinets, granite counters, walk in closet with extra wall closet and custom built icabinets. Family room opens to the garden and pool, it has 78” TV with 4K and built in audio speakers, fireplace and built in cabinets. 4th bedroom has custom built in cabinet and closets it is currently being used as an office. Travertine floors and hardwood maple floors throughout. House was repainted inside and stucco outside. Originally this house was (per assessor’s office) a 5 bedroom home and 2 car garage. In late 2014 the owner remodeled 75% of the house .The owner opted to remove the 5th bedroom and made the garage into a 3 car garage and built 1 lift in order to be able to park 4 cars. Easy access to 280 and 101 and Major Shopping Center. Excellent Las Lomitas School. Must See!

Description

This one level, charming 3-bedroom 2-bathroom home has a gracious living room off the entry with hardwood floors, crown moldings and new fireplace insert. The dining area has a view and access to a lovely large patio with an amazing garden. Kitchen with stainless steel appliances, granite counters and greenhouse window. Dual-glazed windows, 50 year roof, freshly painted inside, and wonderful floor plan.

Subject: Vintage duplex in West-End San Rafael
Reply-To: liz@lizmccarthy.com<mailto:liz@lizmccarthy.com>

[https://d2zhgehghqjuwb.cloudfront.net/accounts/10440/original/1446590019814-r3qnlvmo00s-ea8aa2eabf9d2a2e933dbbda903f24b9.png]






JUST LISTED: 9 F Street, San Rafael
VINTAGE CHARM IN DOWNTOWN SAN RAFAEL






[https://d2zhgehghqjuwb.cloudfront.net/accounts/11218/original/9FStreet05.jpg]





This lovely, legal, vintage 1896 duplex in the West End neighborhood of San Rafael will charm you as soon as you walk in. Desirable, convenient downtown location. Being in this home feels like living in an era where time moved more slowly and craftsmanship was honored. The smart floor plan offers 2 discrete legal units with separate entrances: Upstairs has 2 bedrooms with bonus sun room, large contemporary kitchen with Wedgewood Stove, full bath, hardwood floors and new carpeting. Ground floor has its own 2 or 3 bedrooms, hardwood floors, new carpeting, charming kitchen and full bath. Interior freshly painted. Lovely, flat, landscaped back yard sanctuary gives sense of nature and allows plenty of options for today’s indoor-outdoor lifestyles. Laundry area, large workshop, storage sheds, as well as 2 car off-street parking. Tree lined residential block, but only houses away from the vibrant West End of San Rafael: Yoga, restaurants, Johnny’s Donuts, and more. Sun Valley Elementary School. Possible Expansion Potential (buyer to verify)! Don’t miss out on this rare and charming duplex today!








PROPERTY FEATURES:
• 2 BR + Sunroom/1BA Upstairs
• 2BR /1BA Downstairs
• Legal Duplex
• Wedgwood Stove
• Lovely flat back yard
• Incredible west-end location
• Downtown San Rafael
• Laundry room in basement
• Workshop and sheds
• 2 Car off street parking
• 1962 SqFt House
• 4520 SqFt lot

BROKERS OPEN HOUSE
Weds., May, 23rd 11am-2pm

Open House

Description

Paradise found! This one has it all: Massive 111" television with awesome acoustics in the media playroom. Step outside and the views are amazing. Outdoor living room features a big screen TV, fireplace, ceiling fans and large dining area. Screen walls drop down for shade or to block the wind. Lounge in the shallow end of the swimming pool complete with umbrellas for shade while enjoying the waterfall as it cascades in the deep end. Too hot? Take the water slide for a ride and plunge into the cool waters. Hungry? The outdoor kitchen has it all: wood fired pizza oven, large BBQ, 2 refrigerators, ice maker, motorized shade cover and so much more. Like cars? The 6 car garage is for you! The 4167 SF home has 4 bedrooms and 3 1/2 baths, formal dining room, family room and gourmet kitchen. The hand scraped floors in the family room and kitchen are gorgeous. Plantation shutters in most rooms. Lush landscaping and lots of mature trees compliment the stunning exterior. A must see!
